### 🟠 WARN
1. **ticket: AE-0312** — The ticket's "Known Gap" section (lines 484-504) claims brand-new projects won't fire casing rules live at content review until `get_initial_carousel_state`/`FailClosedReviewCommand.policy_version` thread the project column. **AE-0311's deliverable 3 appears to have closed this gap**: `editorial_workflow_service._resolve_presentation_policy_version` (line 183) reads the project column and seeds `overrides["presentation_policy_version"]` at workflow start (line 139); `phase_artifact_runner._state_policy_version` (line 83) → `ContentReviewContext.policy_version` (line 321) → `FailClosedReviewCommand.policy_version`. The AE-0312 ticket prose was not updated to reflect this. **Risk:** a future reader assumes the gap is open and re-implements the threading (duplicate work / collision). Recommend updating the AE-0312 Known Gap section or adding a note that AE-0311 closed it, plus a dedicated live-content-review integration test that asserts v2 casing warnings fire for a fresh project end-to-end (the components are individually tested but the full chain isn't pinned by a single integration test).

